str2: Nay rather; indeed, truly, really. From Not Used and oun and ge; so then at least.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
A primary interjection; as a sign of the vocative case, O; as a note of exclamation, oh.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To contradict, reply against, give a hostile answer. From anti and apokrinomai; to contradict or dispute.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A thing formed or fashioned. From plasso; something moulded.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: Probably a fuller form of rheo; an alternate for epo in certain tenses; to utter, i.e. Speak or say.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Dative Masculine Singular
str2: To form, mould, as a potter his clay. A primary verb; to mould, i.e. Shape or fabricate.

str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.

str2: (a) I make, manufacture, construct, (b) I do, act, cause. Apparently a prolonged form of an obsolete primary; to make or do.

str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
